  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001_15",
    "text": "A−4 In order to have y(x) = aφ (x) for all x, we must in par- ticular have this for x = e, and so we take a = φ(e)−1. We fi rst note that",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5223529411764706,
      0.38727272727272727,
      0.9192156862745098,
      0.4309090909090909
    ],
    "page": "exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001",
    "order": 10
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_1997_Solutions_1997s_page_001_6",
    "text": "",
